abstract.text: This object defines account permissions for users who are associated with the account permission profile.
users may specify sequential signing recipients when they send documents by using the API.
users can access the account by using the eSignature API.
This object defines account permissions for users who are associated with the account permission profile.
users can send envelopes on behalf of others.
users can be recipients of envelopes transferred to them by administrators of other accounts.
users have full administrative access to the account.
the DocuSign Desktop Client is enabled for users.
users can manage documents by using the API.
Specifies the level of access that users have to account templates. Valid values are:   - `none`  - `use` - `create` - `share`
senders can require recipients to accept supplemental documents.
senders can require recipients to read supplemental documents.
senders are notified when recipients view the documents that they send.
the sequential signing user interface is enabled.
PowerForm Administrators can access all of the PowerForm envelopes associated with the account.
the tagger palette is visible during the sending and correct flows and users can add tabs to documents.
Specifies the level of access that users have to the account's address book. Valid values are:  - `personal` - `useShared` - `usePersonalAndShared` - `personalAndShared`
users can require recipients to view supplemental documents.
users can add requests for attachments from signers.
The PowerForms rights associated with the account permission profile. Valid values are:  - `none`  - `user`  - `admin`
senders receive emails about completed, self-signed documents that contain links to the completed documents instead of PDF attachments.
auto-tagging is enabled for the account.
senders can set the language of the email that is sent to recipients.

users can override the default account setting that controls whether recipients can sign documents on paper. The option to overrride this setting occurs during the sending process on a per-envelope basis.
bulk sending is enabled for users.
